
'''= "Digital Social Innovation is a type of collaborative innovation in which innovators, users and communities co-create knowledge and solutions for a wide range of social needs exploiting the network effect of the Internet".'''


European directory of projects at http://digitalsocial.eu/

=Description=

Jon Kingsbury and Peter Baeck:

"The internet is playing an ever-increasing role in how we work, play and relate to each other. As a natural result of this, many of the most exciting new innovations that enable people to collaborate to address societal challenges are being developed online. At Nesta we call this activity digital social innovation (DSI) and it includes a diverse set of services, entrepreneurs and organisations."
(http://www.theguardian.com/media-network/media-network-blog/2014/feb/28/ten-digital-social-innovators-online)


